OL,3,C'Once-in-a-lifetime event': What is a
OL,4,Cnova explosion and how can I see it?
OL,6,FStargazers across the globe may get
OL,7,Fthe chance to see a "once-in-a-
OL,8,Flifetime" cosmic event this summer
OL,9,Fwhen an exploding star system could
OL,10,Flight up the night sky.
OL,12,FA nova explosion of the binary star
OL,13,Fsystem T Corona Borealis (T CrB) is
OL,14,Fpredicted to take place any time from
OL,15,Funtil September and will be so bright
OL,16,Fwill be visible from Earth with the
OL,17,Fnaked eye.
OL,19,FThis is an extremely rare event: the T
OL,20,FCoronae Borealis nova was last seen
OL,21,Ffrom Earth in 1946.
