OL,3,C'Once-in-a-lifetime event': What is a
OL,4,Cnova explosion and how can I see it?
OL,6,FIt is 3,000 light years away from
OL,7,FEarth, and is made up of two types of
OL,8,Fstar. One, a white dwarf, is an earth-
OL,9,Fsized dead star, and the other is an
OL,10,Fancient red giant.
OL,12,FThe gravitational pull of the white
OL,13,Fdwarf gradually strips away hydrogen
OL,14,Ffrom the red giant.
OL,16,FEventually, this build up of gas
OL,17,Ftriggers a huge thermonuclear
OL,18,Fexplosion, known as a nova explosion.
OL,20,FIs it a supernova?
