OL,3,C'Once-in-a-lifetime event': What is a
OL,4,Cnova explosion and how can I see it?
OL,6,FThis is a different event to a
OL,7,Fsupernova, which involves a final
OL,8,Fexplosion of a dying star.
OL,10,FIn a nova event such as this, the star
OL,11,Fstays intact. The cycle of explosions,
OL,12,Fwhich send the buildup of material
OL,13,Fhurtling off into , can carry on for
OL,14,Fhundreds of thousands of years.
OL,16,FWhy is it so rare?
