OL,3,C'Once-in-a-lifetime event': What is a
OL,4,Cnova explosion and how can I see it?
OL,6,FT Coronae Borealis' nova explosions
OL,7,Fare on a shorter cycle than average.
OL,8,FIt is uncommon to see a repeated
OL,9,Foutburst within our lifetime,
OL,10,Fespecially one so close to our solar
OL,11,Fsystem, NASA said.
OL,13,FThe first recorded sighting of the
OL,14,Fexplosion was from Germany in 1217.
OL,15,FThe T Coronae Borealis nova was last
OL,16,Fseen from Earth in 1946.
